commit.message:
Use std::to_string instead of std::ostringstream.

In some systems locales are messing with number serialization,
so the serialize / deserialize breaks and calls don't work.

threading: set thread names on OpenBSD

While here, use `#if defined()` rather than `#ifdef` like the rest of the code.
logging: fix systemVersion detection on OpenBSD

audio: Build on OpenBSD

OpenBSD supports PulseAudio and OpenAL, but not ALSA.
Either PulseAudio or ALSA are required for libtgvoip.

Add missing OS macros to enable building with
`LIBTGVOIP_DISABLE_PULSEAUDIO=ON` `LIBTGVOIP_DISABLE_ALSA=OFF` as tested
on OpenBSD/amd64 7.2-current.
use genuie webrtc instead of grishka-webrtc-copy-paste legacy
Fix warning in GCC on C++20.
Linux uses its own alloca.h, all others use original UNIX stdlib.h.

Support pthread_setname_np() on FreeBSD and while here use
positive logic in the ifdefs.
Use correct __FreeBSD__ define. Add one more missing.
Use correct __FreeBSD__ define. Add one more missing.
Fix build with unused variable warning.
fixed crash when micro doesn't exist
